The paper deals with lower bounds for dimensionality reduction, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on the Johnson-Lindenstrauss lemma and the use of geometric arguments suggest that the paper is most likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of probabilistic arguments and the mention of previous work on the topic also suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of norms and distances suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possible sub-category.
